# Built binaries
/satelle
/cmd/satelle/satelle

# satelle's own .satelle/ local state is governed by the managed block below
# (added by `satelle init`): the local database is ignored, while the committed
# satelle.toml and the authored markdown under .satelle/ stay tracked — satelle
# dogfoods itself.

# >>> satelle (managed) >>>
# satelle's per-repo database is local state — ignore it and its sidecars, plus
# the per-user config overlay. The committed satelle.toml and the authored
# markdown under .satelle/ stay tracked.
.satelle/satelle.db
.satelle/satelle.db-wal
.satelle/satelle.db-shm
.satelle/satelle.local.toml
# the per-story markdown mirror is regenerated from the local database (the
# source of truth); the files are portable but not versioned in this repo.
.satelle/stories/
# <<< satelle (managed) <<<

# commit-push gate artifacts — the PR-style commit summaries the commit-push
# reviewer writes are generated and read locally per story; they are review
# artifacts, not version-controlled.
.satelle/documents/commit-summary-*.md
